A ROBBERY bid went wrong when a man tried to hold up a busy fish and chip shop. Man facing jail over chip shop raid bid A ROBBERY bid went wrong when a man tried to hold up a busy fish and chip shop.Sean Kelly demanded cash from staff at Adriano's in Clydebank, West Dunbartonshire, as customers queued for their food.Kelly, 29, threatened to jump over the counter but two delivery drivers man-handled him to the groundKelly is facing jail after he admitted attempted robbery at the High Court in Glasgow.He was remanded in custody and will be sentenced next month. 